text: French Canadian (Canadien or Canadien fran√ßais in French) refers to a nation or ethnic group that comes from Canada in the period of French colonization in the 1600s. They are the main French-speaking population of Canada. It may also refer to people of French descent living in Canada, or native speakers of French in Canada. ==References== ==Other websites== *Multicultural Canada website includes seven full-text searchable French Canadian newspapers from Ontario and Quebec Category:Ethnic groups in Canada
